<Issue id="31282" key="FABC-321" number="321" project="10607" reporter="rameshthoomu" assignee="rameshthoomu" creator="rameshthoomu" type="10004" summary="Fabric-ca dependent images should always get the latest fabric images" priority="2" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2018-06-21 23:29:50.0" updated="2019-03-19 11:13:06.0" resolutiondate="2018-07-02 14:08:03.0" votes="0" watches="2" workflowId="32501"> <description><! CDATA Fabric-ca dependent images should always get the latest fabric images while building.  In fabric-ca, *images/fabric-ca-peer/Dockerfile.in* below lines are fetching the PREV_VERSION of the fabric images {code:java} FROM _NS_/fabric-peer:_FABRIC_TAG_{code} {code:java} PROJECT_NAME = fabric-ca BASE_VERSION = 1.2.0 PREV_VERSION = 1.1.0 IS_RELEASE = false  ARCH=$(shell go env GOARCH) MARCH=$(shell go env GOOS)-$(shell go env GOARCH) ifneq ($(IS_RELEASE),true) EXTRA_VERSION ?= snapshot-$(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD) PROJECT_VERSION=$(BASE_VERSION)-$(EXTRA_VERSION) FABRIC_TAG ?= $(ARCH)-$(PREV_VERSION) else PROJECT_VERSION=$(BASE_VERSION) FABRIC_TAG ?= $(ARCH)-$(BASE_VERSION) endif{code} While building fabric-ca dependent images like (fabric-ca-peer, fabric-ca-orderer, fabric-ca-tools) images, the images are building on top of the PREV_VERSION which is 1.1.0 instead of the latest fabric images.  ></description> </Issue>
